3^4=81\equiv1\pmod{10}
\implies 3^{4n}\equiv1
37\equiv7\pmod{10}\implies 37^{98}\equiv7^{98}\pmod{10}
7^4\equiv1\pmod{10}\implies 7^{4n}\equiv1
3^{100}\cdot37^{98}=(3^4)^{25}\cdot(7^4)^{24}\cdot7^2\equiv1\cdot1\cdot9\pmod{10}
